cs.SE, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with managing requirements in software development and proposes an approach for handling software quality.
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on the development of software systems and proposes an approach for managing quality requirements.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper may involve discussing programming languages used in the case study or the approach proposed.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the impact of software quality on society, particularly in the context of the automotive case study.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the role of human factors in managing quality requirements and the usability of the approach proposed.
